= Unordered Lists

Unordered lists display items with bullet points.

== Basic Unordered List

* First item
* Second item
* Third item

== Unordered List with Title

.Unordered List: Features
* Feature one
* Feature two
* Feature three

== Nested Unordered Lists

* First level item
** Second level item
** Another second level item
*** Third level item
*** Another third level item
* Back to first level

== Unordered List with Multiple Paragraphs

* First item

  This is a continuation paragraph for the first item.

* Second item

  This is a continuation paragraph for the second item.

== Unordered List with Mixed Content

* Item with *bold* text
* Item with _italic_ text
* Item with `monospaced` text
* Item with a link: https://example.com

== Unordered List with Nested Ordered List

* First unordered item

  . Ordered nested item
  . Another ordered item

* Second unordered item

  . More ordered items
  . And another

== Complex Nested Lists

* Level 1, Item 1
** Level 2, Item 1
*** Level 3, Item 1
*** Level 3, Item 2
** Level 2, Item 2
* Level 1, Item 2

== Unordered List with Hyphens

- Alternative syntax item
- Another item
- Third item

